mimalloc: A fast memory allocator, optimized for language runtimes that use
reference counting.

https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2019/06/mimalloc-tr-v1.pdf

Sam Gross is the author of 'nogil', a fork of CPython that removes the GIL,
and uses mimalloc for performance.

"Notes From the Meeting On Python GIL Removal Between Python Core and Sam Gross"
